      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 150°C fan (170°C conventional). Double-line a 20 cm round tin with baking paper. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Add {{eggs}} one at a time, beating well between each. Fold in {{plain-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}, then stir in {{sultanas}}, the zests from {{lemon}} and {{orange}}, and {{almond-extract}}. Spoon into the tin and level the surface. Scatter {{blanched-almonds}} over the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 80 to 85 minutes. After the first 40 minutes, if the almonds are colouring faster than the cake is baking, tent loosely with foil. Test with a skewer at 80 minutes; it should come out clean. An oven thermometer is useful for long bakes where an over-hot oven will burn the outside before the centre sets. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes, then on a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "If you add glacé cherries: rinse 100 g in warm water, dry them on kitchen paper, quarter them, and toss in a tablespoon of flour from the recipe before folding in with the sultanas. This reduces (but does not eliminate) the chance of sinking.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The cake slices cleanly when fully cold, not when still warm from the oven.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Replacing 50 g of the plain flour with ground almonds gives a moister, slightly denser result and a more pronounced almond note.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
